## Context
Two small polish items for the streaming render pipeline:

## Part 1: CSS streaming cursor
Add a blinking block cursor to the message container while streaming is active. Pure CSS — zero JS overhead.

```css
@keyframes ava-cursor-blink {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
  50% { opacity: 0; }
}

.streaming-cursor > *:last-child::after {
  content: '▋';
  display: inline-block;
  animation: ava-cursor-blink 1s step-end infinite;
  color: hsl(var(--primary));
  margin-left: 1px;
}
```

Add this to the global stylesheet or a Tailwind plugin. Apply `streaming-cursor` class to the message content container when `isStreaming` is true, remove it when false.

**Gotcha:** The `::after` must be on the last child element (e.g. `prose > *:last-child::after`) not the container itself, otherwise it renders after the block — not inline with the last character.

## Part 2: Post-completion static render handoff
Once `isComplete` is true, convert the message to static HTML using `marked` + DOMPurify. React never re-reconciles completed messages.

```tsx
import { marked } from 'marked';
import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';

const finalHtml = useMemo(
  () => isComplete ? DOMPurify.sanitize(marked(content) as string) : null,
  [isComplete, content] // only recalculates once — when isComplete flips to true
);

if (finalHtml) {
  return (
    <div
      className="prose prose-sm dark:prose-invert"
      dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: finalHtml }}
    />
  );
}
// Streaming render below...
```

Install `marked` and `dompurify` + `@types/dompurify` if not already present.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Blinking cursor visible during streaming, gone on completion
- Cursor renders inline with last text character (not as a block below)
- Completed messages render as static HTML via marked + DOMPurify
- DOMPurify is always applied — no raw marked output in dangerouslySetInnerHTML
- `marked` and `dompurify` added to package.json if missing
- TypeScript clean

